text: A dog is a domesticated animal that is part of the canine family. Dogs are known for their loyalty, intelligence, and affection for their owners. They are often used as working animals, such as for herding, guarding, and search and rescue. Dogs come in a variety of sizes, shapes, and colors, and can be found in many different breeds.

text: NATO was created in 1949 as a response to the threat of Soviet expansionism in Europe. It was designed to provide a collective security system for its members, allowing them to respond to any aggression with a unified response. NATO has since grown to include 29 member states and is seen as a cornerstone of international security.
